HEADWORD: Gummer
<hw>Gum"mer</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[From <er>2d
Gum</er>.]</ety> <def>A punch-cutting tool, or machine for deepening and
enlarging the spaces between the teeth of a worn saw.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Gummiferous</ent>⟦br⟧
